name: document-structure-best-practices.mdc
description: Guidelines for structuring Markdown documents
globs: "*.md"

- Maintain a clear hierarchical structure in each .md file
- Start with a main heading (h1) for an overview
- Use h2 for main sections, h3-h4 for details
- Use bullet points for short lists, tables for structured data or comparisons
- Include a brief summary for each major section 